{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|すべ}}

{{IPAfont|⟨sume<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/sume/}} → {{IPAchar|/sube/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=すべ|-}}, as a shift from older ''sume''.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Previously thought to be derived as the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei|pos=stem or continuative form}} of {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=すべ|-}} verb {{m|ja|統ぶ|tr=subu}}, modern {{m|ja|統べる|tr=suberu||to [[control]], to [[govern]], to [[rule]]}}.  However, later research into {{w|Jōdai Tokushu Kanazukai|ancient phonetic spellings}} clarified that the ''be'' portion of the verb was realized as {{IPAfont|⟨be<sub>2</sub>⟩}}.  During the Old Japanese stage, {{IPAfont|⟨be<sub>2</sub>⟩}} could only have derived phonetically from {{IPAfont|⟨me<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, and not from the {{IPAfont|⟨me<sub>1</sub>⟩}} syllable of the noun.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

